comment.author: 47201412@N02
comment._content: Sydney Morning Herald, Thursday 26 March 1908 (column 4, halfway down): TO-DAY. GLOUCESTER-STREET. IMPORTANT SALE BUILDING MATERIALS. Demolition of 3-story Hotel and adj. Premises. By Order of the Rocks Resumption Board. GLOUCESTER-STREET, corner of Little Essex-street, near Circular Quay, on "Rocks." The first-class Materials of above will be sold BY UNRESERVED PUBLIC AUCTION TO-DAY, THURSDAY, AT 11A.M., comprising:- 500 Sheets GALVD. IRON, 5ft to 9ft lengths. 600 Loads Squared Dimension Stone. Hardwood Girders, Story Posts, Battens. 50 Boxframes and Sashes, Bar Windows, Entrances. Counters, Fittings, Door Jambs, Casements. 6000ft 6 x 1 sq. jointed Hardwood Flooring, sound. 5000ft H'wood Rafters and Studs, 4 x 2 1/2, 4 x 2, 3 x 2. 6000ft H.W. Joists, 9 x 3, 8 x 3, 6 x 2 1/2 1000ft Lining, Partition Boards, Cedar Skirting, Archi- traves, 30 Panel 1/2 glass and Ledge Doors and Jambs Bal. Rails, Ver. Posts. 6 x 6, chamfd., Mantels. Two 8 x 4 IRON GIRDERS, 22ft long. Sanitary Ware, Downpipe, and a host of SUNDRIES. A. BARNETT AND PUGH have been instructed to sell the above, in lots to suit purchasers. TERMS CASH. Auctioneers' Office: 82 Queen-street, Woollahra. - trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/14934921
